04880nam a22007575i 9780231548557DE-B159720210526051534.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210526t20202020nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a2019050913  a97802315485577 a10.7312/eker189802doi  a(DE-B1597)563205  a(OCoLC)1145098881  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY00aTX324b.E34 2020 7aSOC0130002bisacsh04a648/.52231 aEkerdt, David, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aDownsizing :bConfronting Our Possessions in Later Life /cDavid Ekerdt. 1aNew York, NY : bColumbia University Press, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource :b2 b&w figures  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tIntroduction: Not Forever -- t1. A Convoy of Possessions Across the Life Course -- t2. With Aging, How Large a Convoy? -- t3. Moving Calls the Question -- t4. Contours of House hold Disbandment -- t5. Gifts to Others -- t6. Selling Possessions -- t7. Donations and Discards -- t8. Emotion and Evaluation -- t9. Advice -- tAppendix -- tNotes -- tReferences -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAs life unfolds, things tend to accumulate. When older adults undergo health, residential, and marital changes, they will face a reckoning with their lifelong store of possessions—special, ordinary, and forgotten. Such a predicament now confronts tens of millions of Americans as the Baby Boom cohort passes into retirement and beyond. Despite what a thriving industry of clutter manuals tells us, for most older adults, downsizing is no simple task.Drawing on in-depth interviews with recent movers in over a hundred diverse U.S. households, David Ekerdt analyzes the downsizing process and what it says about the meaning and management of possessions. He details how households approach and accomplish downsizing, exploring the decision-making process and the effectiveness of different strategies. From an expert gerontological perspective, he considers the cognitive, physical, emotional, and social tasks that the process entails and the role of factors such as gender and class on the divestment of things. Ekerdt finds that despite the fatigue and emotional challenges people encounter, afterward they report satisfaction in having completed a downsizing and feel empowerment on the other side of the task. Offering an empathetic and practical look at one of life’s major transitions, Downsizing brings forward the voices of elders so that older adults, their families and friends, and practitioners working with older clients can understand and benefit from their experience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aHouse cleaning. 0aOlder peoplexConduct of life. 0aOrderliness. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311071097708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/eker1898040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231548557423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231548557.jpg  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-071097-7  CUP Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPAL